00:39:55,076 --> 00:39:59,846
I got to fix two dislocated shoulders,
and save a leg from amputation.

686
00:39:59,948 --> 00:40:04,450
<i>Problem is... we're human.</i>

687
00:40:04,552 --> 00:40:07,287
<i>We want more
than just to survive.</i>

688
00:40:07,388 --> 00:40:10,223
- Were you staring
at Sloan again?
- Oh!

689
00:40:10,325 --> 00:40:12,885
The... The baby.
Did you see her?

690
00:40:12,944 --> 00:40:16,779
- How did the interview go?
- I'm out.

691
00:40:16,881 --> 00:40:19,465
- What? What happened?
- It's a long story. It's fine.

692
00:40:19,567 --> 00:40:22,168
Seriously, I'm OK with it.

693
00:40:23,255 --> 00:40:26,989
I have you, what else do I need?

694
00:40:32,130 --> 00:40:33,896
<i>We want love.</i>

695
00:40:41,506 --> 00:40:43,439
Hey.

696
00:40:45,076 --> 00:40:47,076
Hi.

697
00:40:47,912 --> 00:40:50,279
Hi, Zola.

698
00:40:52,083 --> 00:40:54,650
I'm Meredith.

699
00:40:54,752 --> 00:40:57,487
I'm hoping to be your mama.

700
00:41:02,293 --> 00:41:03,993
<i>We want success.</i>

701
00:41:04,095 --> 00:41:06,045
You know it's
gonna be Mer, right?

702
00:41:07,615 --> 00:41:10,966
It doesn't mean that you're a
bad surgeon or a bad doctor.

703
00:41:11,068 --> 00:41:14,137
Some people just
don't fit the bill.

704
00:41:14,239 --> 00:41:19,342
They're better at other things. Like
you and those kids, you're good at that.

705
00:41:19,444 --> 00:41:22,494
But between you and
Mer? She's organized.

706
00:41:22,597 --> 00:41:26,866
People like her, people
trust her, she's a natural.

707
00:41:26,985 --> 00:41:30,403
- People trust her.
- I'm just saying,

708
00:41:30,505 --> 00:41:33,539
go steal your job
back. Go to Africa.

709
00:41:33,641 --> 00:41:36,209
That's what you're good at.
Go do what you're good at.

710
00:41:36,311 --> 00:41:39,612
<i>We want to be the
best that we can be.</i>

711
00:41:39,714 --> 00:41:43,049
OK, I know you're mad, but you
can't just sit here and drink all night.

712
00:41:43,151 --> 00:41:45,317
So I'm gonna take you home...

713
00:41:48,056 --> 00:41:50,389
I... I was not expecting that.

714
00:41:50,491 --> 00:41:52,158
You told me to be excellent.

715
00:41:52,861 --> 00:41:54,627
So I'm gonna be.

716
00:41:54,729 --> 00:41:57,230
I'm gonna be an
excellent surgeon.

717
00:41:57,331 --> 00:42:00,399
And I'm gonna be
excellent in bed tonight.

718
00:42:02,254 --> 00:42:05,521
<i>So we fight like hell
to get those things.</i>

719
00:42:07,592 --> 00:42:09,058
All right, Karev?

720
00:42:10,227 --> 00:42:12,628
Meredith messed with
the Alzheimer's trial.

721
00:42:14,382 --> 00:42:17,233
<i>Anything else feels...</i>

722
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:20,120
<i>like death.</i>
